Text: Ah, the joyous occasion of Antarctica's birthday, where it’s all fun and games until someone mentions climate change.
As I sip my tea, I can't help but observe the merriment around cake—and the hints of curry.
But dear mates, we’re belting out a birthday tune while the planet’s in peril.
Might I suggest we widen our cultural exchange with a bit less frosting and a bit more climate awareness?
Meanwhile, India and America are bound to start an international food fight; I’m just here to pop the kettle on.
Well, it’s like watching a reality show without a remote!
India and America are squabbling over who makes the best curry—can’t we just agree it’s me for the tea?
Meanwhile, Antarctica’s birthday bash turns into a lament when someone brings up climate change.
I pop the kettle on and patch it up with light banter, but everyone knows I've misplaced my relevance.
Still trying to charm with my posh accent while the world’s out there playing international chess.
Not exactly the empire I used to rule, but at least tea’s still a thing!
